Thanks for the advice @m3bm3b ! Is that the one in https://github.com/google/nsync? I am not sure if I am doing it right: 
I first ran `mkmakefile.sh` and it said `x86_64.macos.clang` already existed so I ran `make` in that folder. No errors pop up. Then I tried installing tensorflow v.1.4.0rc1 again but got the same error. I must be missing something!
